<HEADLINE>
<P>
MALATHION TESTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
From the Metro article (Aug. 29) on malathion: "In an interview, (Los Angeles 
County health official Dr. Paul) Papanek said the urine testing is being done 
to support the state's contention that the amount of malathion absorbed by the 
body after spraying does not pose a health threat." 
</P>
<P>
What kind of science is this? Bad, unscientific and a definite conflict of 
interest. Self-monitoring or self-testing are no substitutes for independent 
assessments. 
</P>
<P>
Whether it's the self-monitoring by agencies of their sewage being discharged 
into Santa Monica Bay or justifying a state policy to spray malathion over an 
unwilling and vulnerable populace, we must insist on impartial, truly 
scientific evaluations. 
</P>
<P>
ELLEN STERN HARRIS 
</P>
<P>
Executive Director 
</P>
<P>
Fund for the Environment 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
