<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
H. J. Heinz Co.: The Pittsburgh-based food company announced first-quarter net 
income of $143.2 million, up 13.2% from the same quarter last year. Revenue for 
the quarter was $1.56 billion, up 7.4% from the first quarter of 1989. The 
company attributed the increases to higher prices, favorable foreign exchange 
rate and strong performances by the company's major brands in their respective 
markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA091190-0015 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 274254 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
