<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Optical Radiation Corp.: The company said net income for fiscal 1990 totaled 
$7.3 million, up 64% from the year before. 
</P>
<P>
Sales rose 19% to $130.1 million. Profit was reduced by a $6.7-million charge 
related to an adverse decision in a patent litigation case. The Azusa-based 
company said the earnings rise reflected significant contributions from its 
consumer optical group and improved performance from its ophthalmic surgical 
products group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
