<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Standard Logic Inc.: The Anaheim-based manufacturer of electronic assemblies 
and systems reported a third-quarter net loss of $30,548, contrasted with net 
income of $239,334 for the like 1989 period. 
</P>
<P>
Sales for the quarter ended July 28 dropped 71% to $211,882 from $730,295. For 
the nine-month period, the company lost $139,785, compared to a loss of 
$285,460 a year earlier. Sales declined 49% to $676,260 from $1.3 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
