<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
* Bishop Inc. said its directors elected James R. Schwartz as president and 
chief executive of the Agoura Hills concern, which provides design products and 
services for engineers and architects. 
</P>
<P>
Schwartz succeeded John J. Theiss, who resigned to pursue other interests, said 
Bishop, which has struggled in recent years. In the nine months that ended June 
30, Bishop lost $872,000 on revenue of $7.53 million. 
</P>
<P>
Bishop's chairman is Richard M. Drysdale, who also is chairman of Terminal Data 
Corp., a Moorpark maker of imaging equipment that also is ailing financially. 
</P>
<P>
Schwartz formerly was president of Terminal Data and in recent months had been 
a consultant to Bishop. 
</P>
</TEXT>
