</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
* Terminal Data Corp., a struggling Moorpark maker of electronic imaging 
equipment, named Jeffrey A. Wilson president and chief executive, effective 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
He succeeds David W. Krar Hutton, who quit in July, and Wilson becomes Terminal 
Data's fourth president in as many years. 
</P>
<P>
Wilson formerly was president of Adaptive Information Systems, a division of 
the Japanese computer and electronics giant Hitachi Ltd. He also was president 
of the records management division of Bell &amp; Howell. 
</P>
