<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: JET CRAFT USA PLANS PUBLIC STOCK OFFERING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jet Craft USA Inc., a start-up company in Las Vegas that hopes to develop a 
six-seat business jet, plans to raise about $25 million with an initial public 
stock offering of 5 million common shares, according to a company filing with 
the Securities and Exchange Commission. 
</P>
<P>
Jet Craft is headed by John E. Morgan, a former pilot, and Floyd E. Snow, owner 
of Aircraft Technical Service Inc., a Van Nuys company involved in designing 
the proposed aircraft, the filing said. 
</P>
<P>
Proceeds from the offering will be used to design, produce, test and market the 
plane, the filing said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
