<P>
(900) NEW KIDS: A federal judge in Los Angeles dismissed lawsuits filed by the 
pop group New Kids on the Block against USA Today and a tabloid magazine, 
ruling that the band's image can be used by the publications to promote 
900-line telephone polls. In dismissing the lawsuits on Monday, U.S. District 
Judge William Rea found that, as news-gathering organizations, USA Today and 
the Star magazine are permitted to use the group's trademarks to conduct polls 
and surveys. The publications are protected under the First Amendment from the 
group's claims of trademark infringement, false advertising and unfair 
competition. BETH KLEID 
</P>
