<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALL NETWORKS WILL CARRY BUSH'S TALK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush's address to a joint session of Congress tonight will be carried 
by the major television networks and Cable News Network. 
</P>
<P>
Representatives of ABC, CBS, NBC and CNN said they will interrupt regular 
programming for the 6 p.m. PDT speech, in which Bush is to discuss Persian Gulf 
policy and his meeting with Soviet President Mikhail S. Gorbachev. 
</P>
</TEXT>
