<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: L.A. TOLD TO COORDINATE MEDFLY SUIT WITH 4 
OTHERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A judge on Monday ordered the city of Los Angeles to coordinate its lawsuit to 
block malathion spraying with four other similar cases before it interviews 
state scientists involved in the effort to eradicate the Mediterranean fruit 
fly. 
</P>
<P>
Judge John Zebrowski, who is also handling the other legal challenges, told 
attorneys on both sides of the cases to meet by Sept. 18 and establish a 
schedule for collecting information from state scientists and agencies. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles, Glendale and Burbank are trying to stop the use of malathion on 
the grounds that it violates state laws requiring proper notification of 
residents before each spraying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
