<HEADLINE>
<P>
METS GET SCHATZEDER FROM ASTROS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The New York Mets acquired left-hander Dan Schatzeder from the Houston Astros 
Monday for minor leaguers Steve LaRose and Nick Davis. 
</P>
<P>
Schatzeder, 35, is 1-3 this season with a 2.39 earned-run average in 45 games, 
all but two in relief. 
</P>
<P>
He is 69-68 in 13 major league seasons. 
</P>
<P>
LaRose was 1-1 with a 3.57 ERA and seven saves at St. Lucie of the Florida 
State League and 1-3 with a 3.90 ERA in 19 games at Jackson of the Texas 
League. Davis batted .263 with six home runs and 48 runs batted in for 
Pittsfield of the New York-Penn Rookie League. 
</P>
<P>
LaRose was assigned to Tucson of the Pacific Coast League, and Davis was 
assigned to Asheville, N.C., of the South Atlantic League. Associated Press 
</P>
</TEXT>
