<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: BEN JOHNSON AIMING FOR JANUARY COMEBACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sprinter Ben Johnson, declaring himself fit and drug-free, said Monday that he 
will begin his comeback in January after a two-year suspension for steroid use. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson said he wants to win the world and Olympic titles in the next two years 
and regain the world record in the 100 meters. 
</P>
<P>
"I want to take back the titles and the records I have been deprived of," 
Johnson said, adding that his first meet would be the Hamilton Spectator Games 
at Hamilton, Canada, Jan. 11. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson, who said he plans to run in at least 13 indoor competitions in 1991, 
was stripped of the Olympic 100-meter title and of the world record after 
testing positive for steroids at Seoul in September of 1988. His suspension 
expires Sept. 24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
