<P>
3 CLOTHING STORE THEFT SUSPECTS HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three people were arrested Monday on suspicion of burglary after police found 
$10,000 worth of stolen clothing in their car, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The merchandise was stolen from at least 10 retail clothing stores in Irvine 
and Tustin, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The three were stopped about 4:30 p.m. by Irvine Police Officer Clint McCall 
because they matched a broadcast description of suspects who had just 
burglarized the Public Image Clothing store at 3850 Barranca Parkway. 
</P>
<P>
One of the suspects admitted to the thefts and said they were stealing clothes 
for "personal use" for their back-to-school wardrobes, McCall said. 
</P>
<P>
Arrested on 10 counts of burglary were Sharla Thomas, 33, of Oceanside; Alfred 
Childress, 22, of Escondido, and Sunday Bishop, 32, of Orange. They were taken 
to Orange County Jail where they were being held in lieu of $10,000 bail each. 
</P>
