</P>
<P>
TRI-CITY RECYCLING PROGRAM PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eager to ease the flow of trash into overflowing landfills and meet a looming 
state limit on waste disposal, three South County cities are gearing up to 
begin curbside recycling programs in their communities. 
</P>
<P>
Flanked by brand-new recycling trucks, the mayors of San Juan Capistrano, San 
Clemente and Dana Point will unfurl plans for the recycling effort during a 
ceremony at San Juan Capistrano City Hall today at 2 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The three cities are launching the recycling programs in an effort to meet a 
new state law that requires all municipalities to reduce solid waste levels by 
1995. Cities that do not comply with the state mandate could be hit with 
substantial fines. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
