<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' ATHLETE OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Will Bohuslavizki 
</P>
<P>
School: Estancia High School 
</P>
<P>
Sport: Football 
</P>
<P>
Position: Receiver 
</P>
<P>
Height: 5-8 
</P>
<P>
Weight: 150 
</P>
<P>
In a single game, Bohuslavizki, a senior, surpassed his reception total of last 
season and tied the Estancia single-game reception record. A non-starter last 
year -- he had only eight receptions -- Bohuslavizki moved into Estancia's 
starting lineup Thursday and caught 11 of Matt Johner's passes for 269 yards 
and three touchdowns to help the Eagles rally to defeat Los Amigos, 30-27. 
</P>
<P>
Bohuslavizki had five receptions for 138 yards and two touchdowns -- one of 50 
yards, the other of 14 with 34 seconds remaining -- in the final three minutes 
of the game. "We kept throwing it," Estancia Coach John Liebengood said. "And 
they didn't make any adjustments. They didn't do anything different. 
Consequently, he kept catching the ball." 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Other top performers: 
</P>
<P>
* Brent Austin, an El Modena cross-country runner who ran 16 minutes 17.6 
seconds for three miles to finish second in the Bronco Classic Saturday and 
lead El Modena to the team title. 
</P>
<P>
* Kennedy's Vince Church, who rushed 25 times for 255 yards, ran for three 
touchdowns, caught a pass for another and made an interception in Kennedy's 
26-14 victory Friday over Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
* Estancia's Matt Johner, who passed for 342 yards and three touchdowns in the 
Eagles' 30-27 victory Thursday over Los Amigos. 
</P>
<P>
* Costa Mesa's Ryan McEvoy, who completed 15 of 25 passes for 294 yards and 
four touchdowns in the Mustangs' 41-7 victory Sunday over Twentynine Palms. 
</P>
<P>
* Mission Viejo quarterback Tim Snowden, who completed each of his 12 passes 
and amassed 208 yards in the first half of a 42-12 victory Friday over Long 
Beach Jordan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Will Bohuslavizki 
</P>
