<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: SCIENCE / TECHNOLOGY; 
</P>
<P>
COMPUTER COMPANIES FIGHTING A LEGAL BATTLE OVER MICROPROCESSOR PATENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Dean Takahashi, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gilbert Hyatt, the La Palma researcher who shook the computer industry two 
weeks ago when he announced that he had received a patent for inventing the 
microprocessor after a 20-year legal fight, isn't the only one seeking 
royalties on microchip technology. 
</P>
<P>
Stan Victor, spokesman for Texas Instruments Inc., said the company is seeking 
to enforce nine microprocessor-related patents that cover basic functions such 
as how a computer's overall system interacts with a microprocessor -- the 
"brains" of a computer and many other electronic devices. 
</P>
<P>
Unlike Hyatt, TI is seeking to enforce patents covering specific microprocessor 
functions rather than a patent on the basic device itself. 
</P>
<P>
"We do not think the Hyatt patent will have any effect on our litigation with 
Zenith Data Systems Corp.," Victor said. TI sued Zenith Data in December for 
patent infringement. 
</P>
<P>
And on Friday, Tandy Corp. filed suit against TI, alleging that the 
Dallas-based firm has violated antitrust laws and has charged excessive fees to 
companies that want to license TI's patented microprocessor technology. Victor 
said the suit is a "typical counterclaim" without merit. 
</P>
<P>
Victor added, however, that TI claims to hold the basic patent on the invention 
of the microprocessor through a patent granted to TI engineer Gary W. Boone on 
Sept. 4, 1973. 
</P>
<P>
He said the company is not yet challenging Hyatt's patent claim in court. But 
with TI unwilling to accept the ruling by the patent office, the two sides 
could be headed for a showdown. 
</P>
<P>
Tandy contends TI's patent is invalid because TI's version of the 
microprocessor was invented after other parties had already invented it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
PATENTS; ROYALTIES; SUITS; TEXAS INSTRUMENTS INC; ZENITH DATA SYSTEMS CORP; 
TANDY CORP 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
