<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 GAZA CHILDREN HURT PLAYING WITH GRENADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM UPI) 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A boy and his sister were seriously injured Monday when a grenade they dug up 
in the Gaza Strip exploded when they started playing catch with it, 
Palestinians said. 
</P>
<P>
The accident happened in the Israeli-occupied territories on the outskirts of 
the Gaza Strip town of Khan Yunis. 
</P>
