<TEXT>
<P>
America has virtually abandoned the seriously mentally ill who cannot afford to 
pay for treatment, says a report released today by two advocacy groups. 
</P>
<P>
More than 250,000 people with schizophrenia and manic-depressive psychosis live 
in public shelters, on the streets and in prisons and jails, the report by 
Public Citizen and the National Alliance for the Mentally Ill said. 
</P>
<P>
Many others among the nation's 2 million seriously mentally ill cannot afford 
medical treatment or adequate housing and live in communities where no 
vocational rehabilitation services are available, the groups say. 
