<TEXT>
<P>
Florida's weekly Lotto jackpot was raised to $90 million today as sales 
continued at a pace that could send the game past the $100-million mark before 
Saturday night's drawing. 
</P>
<P>
Last Saturday there were no winning tickets in a $50-million lottery. 
</P>
<P>
For the jackpot to reach $100 million, lottery officials calculate, the state 
will have to sell $98 million in tickets this week. The record is $56 million 
in sales in one week. 
</P>
<P>
The national record for a lottery prize is $115 million, which was awarded in 
Pennsylvania to 14 ticket-holders, some of them individuals and some groups. 
</P>
<P>
But the U.S. record for the largest single lottery prize goes to Sheelah Ryan 
of Winter Springs, Fla., who won a Lotto jackpot of $55.1 million in 1988. 
