P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
UPI CLOSING BUREAUS IN 5 STATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
United Press International is closing bureaus in five states, according to a 
spokesman for the news service. 
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Milt Capps confirmed a report in today's Albuquerque Tribune that 
bureaus in New Mexico, Wyoming and Montana will be closed. He declined to say 
how many layoffs were involved. 
</P>
<P>
Capps said UPI has also given notice to staffers in one-person bureaus in Grand 
Rapids, Mich., and Bismarck, N.D. 
</P>
<P>
"We are expanding our stringer network in those states and exploring a number 
of joint ventures at the state and regional level," Capps said. 
</P>
<P>
The Tribune said UPI's single-person bureau in Santa Fe is closing Sept. 21 as 
part of shutdowns in the three states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
